## Code Organization

### File Creation
- Only create new `.py` files when implementing new features
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Keep code modular but avoid over-fragmentation

### Testing
- Test files should go in `tests/` directory (when created)
- Temporary test files should be cleaned up after use

---

## Communication

### When Working on Tasks
- Update TODO.md to track progress
- Use code comments for technical details
- Keep user informed via chat, not via creating documentation files

### Completion Reports
- Provide completion summary in chat
- Update TODO.md with completion status
- Do NOT create separate summary files

